						               													<description>This is a game designed for exactly three players played on a triangular board which looks like Serpinski's gasket.  Each player is attempting to get their pieces to their home territory.  The catch is they don't start with any of their pieces, having to rely on their opponents to place them.  During a turn, a player first places a piece from her pool, and then moves one of her pieces on the board by sliding it along the edges of the triangles.  If a player manages to make a triangle of all her color (or white) stones, she gets to remove a piece from the board or move another piece.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
